ns, while WTI remains elevated at $79.20. Energy-linked refinance risk is mounting for high-yield corporates; special-situations investors should monitor covenant headroom and capex flexibility in levered energy and industrial credits over near-term."},{"tag":"Labor","text":"June payrolls collapsed to 57K from 129K, though unemployment held at 4.2%. Initial claims remain sticky at 208K. Wage growth accelerating (AHE +3.52% YoY) signals persistent wage pressure despite cooling job creation\u2014a key risk for margin-squeezed issuers and supporting Fed caution on rate cuts."},{"tag":"Inflation","text":"Headline CPI at 3.46% (down from 4.17%) but core PCE ticked up to 3.41% from 3.32%. PPI easing to 5.51% provides some relief, yet sticky services inflation (ISM Prices Paid 67.7) and energy shock keep disinflationary path uncertain. Speculative-grade credits face input-cost pressure; credit-quality deterioration likely continues."},{"tag":"Policy/Rates","text":"Fed held at 3.75%; yield curve steepening sharply (10y-2y spread to 39bps from 28bps). ECB just raised to 2.25% in June and faces July 23 meeting amid inflation risk. Higher rates are straining refinance access for weaker borrowers; special-situations opportunities emerging in stretched cap structures and liability management activity."},{"tag":"Credit Markets","text":"HY OAS tightened marginally to 269bps; IG OAS at 78bps. Market remains bifurcated: resilient credits trading tight, weaker speculative-grade and private credit facing funding stress. Elevated capital costs are reshaping default expectations, particularly in BSL and highly leveraged private credit. Volatility (VIX 18.65) remains elevated."},{"tag":"Growth","text":"GDPNow tracker at 1.68% (up from 1.24%); Q1 2026 actual GDP was 2.1%. Consumer resilience remains key (retail sales +0.2% m/m in June, control group +0.5%), but momentum is decelerating. Soft labor market and tight financial conditions suggest late-cycle dynamics with modest near-term growth but increased downside tail risk."},{"tag":"Consumer/Housing","text":"Consumer sentiment collapsed to 44.8 from 49.8; savings rate flat at 3.0%. Housing starts jumped to 1,427K in June but existing home sales fell to 4.09M from 4.19M. Mortgage rates at 6.55% weigh on affordability. Divergent K-shaped consumption visible: high-income households benefiting from equity gains, low-income facing debt pressure and inflation impact."}]},"releases":{"fomc":"Jul 29","ecb":"Jul 23","jobs":"Aug 7","ismMfg":"Aug 3","ismServices":"Aug 5","claims":"Weekly (Thu)","cpi":"Aug 12 (est.)","ppi":"Aug 13 (est.)","retail":"Aug 17 (est.)","housing":"Aug 17 (est.)","existing":"Aug 21 (est.)","pce":"Jul 28 (est.)","gdp":"Jul 28 (est.)","umich":"Aug 14 (est.)","chinaPMI":"Jul 31 (est.)","daily":"Daily","gdpnowKey":"Updates ~weekly"},"regime":{"label":"Late-cycle bifurcation","detail":"tight spreads on quality credits, funding stress on private/leveraged credit, energy shock driving sector dispersion, sticky wage inflation, labor cooling, high-income resilience masking low-income deterioration","source":"claude"},"calendar":[{"date":"2026-07-23","display":"Jul 23","label":"ECB rate decision","impact":"med","consensusKey":"ECB"},{"date":"2026-07-23","display":"Jul 23","label":"Initial jobless claims","impact":"low","consensusKey":"Claims"},{"date":"2026-07-28","display":"Jul 28 (est.)","label":"Core PCE & GDP","impact":"high","consensusKey":"PCE"},{"date":"2026-07-29","display":"Jul 29","label":"FOMC rate decision","impact":"high","consensusKey":"FOMC"},{"date":"2026-07-30","display":"Jul 30","label":"Initial jobless claims","impact":"low","consensusKey":"Claims"},{"date":"2026-08-03","display":"Aug 3","label":"ISM Manufacturing PMI","impact":"med","consensusKey":"ISM Mfg"},{"date":"2026-08-05","display":"Aug 5","label":"ISM Services PMI","impact":"med","consensusKey":"ISM Services"},{"date":"2026-08-06","display":"Aug 6","label":"Initial jobless claims","impact":"low","consensusKey":"Claim